<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Ontology> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionIRI> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#imports> <http://rds.posccaesar.org/ontology/lis14/ont/ido-ssn/0.1> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#imports> <https://w3id.org/pko/1.0.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/abstract> "The Manufacturing Quality Troubleshooting Ontology (MQTO) provides a domain-independent semantic framework for modeling manufacturing quality inspection, failure diagnosis, and countermeasure recommendation. Building on the LIS (Lifecycle Information System) specified/actual pattern and integrating SOSA/SSN observation semantics, MQTO enables structured representation of Ishikawa (fishbone) root cause analysis across Machine, Material, and Method categories. The ontology supports both schema-level knowledge (failure types, metrics, countermeasure procedures) and instance-level data (actual observations, failure occurrences, executed remediation steps), making it applicable across diverse manufacturing domains including die-casting, injection molding, machining, and assembly processes."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor> <https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2661-5575> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/created> "2026-03-17"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator> <https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9521-8907> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "A generalised ontology for manufacturing quality troubleshooting, applicable across different manufacturing domains. Covers both the specified (schema-level) and actual (instance-level) layers of a manufacturing process, with a focus on root cause analysis, failure diagnosis, and countermeasure recommendation."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/license> <http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <https://github.com/dg-assist> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/rights> "Copyright 2026 DG Assist. Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject> "Industry 4.0"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject> "Ishikawa diagram"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject> "SOSA"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject> "SSN"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject> "die-casting"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject> "manufacturing"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject> "quality control"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject> "root cause analysis"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject> "troubleshooting"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "Manufacturing Quality Troubleshooting Ontology"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/ontology/bibo/status> <http://purl.org/ontology/bibo/status/draft> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/vocab/vann/preferredNamespacePrefix> "mqto" .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://purl.org/vocab/vann/preferredNamespaceUri> "https://w3id.org/mqto#" .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://schema.org/codeRepository> <https://github.com/dg-assist/mqto> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://schema.org/funding> <https://projekte.ffg.at/projekt/4641766> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://schema.org/logo> <https://dg-assist.github.io/mqto/logo.png> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relationship to Procedural Knowledge Ontology (PKO): mqto countermeasure classes align with PKO procedure modeling patterns. mqto:Countermeasure is a subclass of pko:Procedure, representing remediation procedures in the specified layer. mqto:CountermeasureStep aligns with p-plan:Step for individual actions. In the actual layer, mqto:CountermeasureExecution extends pko:ProcedureExecution and mqto:CountermeasureStepExecution extends pko:StepExecution. Both ontologies follow a specification/execution (plan/actual) pattern, though mqto uses LIS (lis:Specified/lis:Actual with lis:implements) while PKO uses P-PLAN/PROV (with pko:executesProcedure/pko:executesStep). Key architectural difference: mqto externalizes step ordering via mqto:List containers for step reusability across procedures, while PKO embeds ordering directly in steps via pko:nextStep properties."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Manufacturing Quality Troubleshooting Ontology"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo> "1.0.0" .
<https://w3id.org/mqto> <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/homepage> <https://dg-assist.github.io/mqto/> .
