# https://w3id.org/mqto#appearedOn
<https://w3id.org/mqto#appearedOn> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#appearedOn> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureOccurrence> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#appearedOn> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#ActualIshikawaItem> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#appearedOn> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a FailureOccurrence to the specific ActualIshikawaItem (physical machine, material batch, or process execution) where it manifested. Establishes the concrete location or context of the failure event in the actual layer."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#appearedOn> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "appeared on"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#baseFor
<https://w3id.org/mqto#baseFor> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#baseFor> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#basedOn> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#baseFor> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Indicates that an Observation serves as the data foundation for a MetricAssessment calculation. Inverse of basedOn. Enables tracing from raw sensor data to computed metrics."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#baseFor> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "base for"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#basedOn
<https://w3id.org/mqto#basedOn> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#basedOn> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#MetricAssessment> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#basedOn> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Observation> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#basedOn> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a MetricAssessment to the Observation(s) used as input data for its calculation. Establishes the data provenance chain from raw sensor readings to computed metrics. Inverse of baseFor."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#basedOn> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "based on"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedFor
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedFor> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedFor> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#MetricAssessment> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedFor> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#ActualIshikawaItem> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedFor> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a MetricAssessment to the specific ActualIshikawaItem (physical machine, material batch, or process execution) it evaluates. Establishes which concrete entity the metric calculation applies to in the actual layer."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedFor> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "calculated for"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#causedBy
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedBy> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#causes> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureMode> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureMode> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a Failure Mode to another Failure Mode that causes it, forming a causal chain in root cause analysis. This general property has three sub-properties (causedByWeakly, causedByModerately, causedByStrongly) to express different causal strengths. Inverse of causes."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "caused by"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#causedByModerately
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedByModerately> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedByModerately> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#causedBy> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedByModerately> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#causesModerately> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedByModerately> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Indicates a moderate-strength causal relationship where one Failure Mode is caused by another with medium probability or influence. Enables ordinal ranking of causal strengths without requiring precise numeric probabilities. Subproperty of causedBy."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedByModerately> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "caused by moderately"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#causedByStrongly
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedByStrongly> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedByStrongly> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#causedBy> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedByStrongly> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#causesStrongly> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedByStrongly> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Indicates a strong causal relationship where one Failure Mode is caused by another with high probability or significant influence. Enables ordinal ranking of causal strengths without requiring precise numeric probabilities. Subproperty of causedBy."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedByStrongly> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "caused by strongly"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#causedByWeakly
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedByWeakly> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedByWeakly> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#causedBy> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedByWeakly> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#causesWeakly> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedByWeakly> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Indicates a weak causal relationship where one Failure Mode is caused by another with low probability or minor influence. Enables ordinal ranking of causal strengths without requiring precise numeric probabilities. Subproperty of causedBy."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causedByWeakly> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "caused by weakly"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#causes
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causes> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureMode> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureMode> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a Failure Mode to another Failure Mode that it causes, forming a causal chain in root cause analysis. This general property has three sub-properties (causesWeakly, causesModerately, causesStrongly) to express different causal strengths. Inverse of causedBy."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "causes"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#causesModerately
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causesModerately> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causesModerately> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#causes> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causesModerately> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Indicates a moderate-strength causal relationship where one Failure Mode causes another with medium probability or influence. Enables ordinal ranking of causal strengths without requiring precise numeric probabilities. Subproperty of causes."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causesModerately> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "causes moderately"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#causesStrongly
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causesStrongly> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causesStrongly> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#causes> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causesStrongly> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Indicates a strong causal relationship where one Failure Mode causes another with high probability or significant influence. Enables ordinal ranking of causal strengths without requiring precise numeric probabilities. Subproperty of causes."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causesStrongly> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "causes strongly"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#causesWeakly
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causesWeakly> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causesWeakly> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#causes> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causesWeakly> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Indicates a weak causal relationship where one Failure Mode causes another with low probability or minor influence. Enables ordinal ranking of causal strengths without requiring precise numeric probabilities. Subproperty of causes."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#causesWeakly> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "causes weakly"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#evaluatedBy
<https://w3id.org/mqto#evaluatedBy> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#evaluatedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#ObservableProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#evaluatedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#MetricAssessment> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#evaluatedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates an ObservableProperty to the MetricAssessment that evaluated it (actual layer). Inverse of mqto:evaluatesProperty. Counterpart to mqto:readBy in the specified layer."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#evaluatedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "evaluated by"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#evaluatesProperty
<https://w3id.org/mqto#evaluatesProperty> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#evaluatesProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#evaluatedBy> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#evaluatesProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#MetricAssessment> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#evaluatesProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#ObservableProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#evaluatesProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates a MetricAssessment to the ObservableProperty it evaluated (actual layer). Counterpart to mqto:readsFrom, which relates a Metric to a Signal in the specified layer."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#evaluatesProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "evaluates property"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#failureBelongsTo
<https://w3id.org/mqto#failureBelongsTo> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#failureBelongsTo> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#hasFailure> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#failureBelongsTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureMode> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#failureBelongsTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#IshikawaItem> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#failureBelongsTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Associates a Failure Mode with the IshikawaItem (Machine, Material, or Method) category it belongs to in the fishbone diagram structure. Establishes which root cause category the failure is classified under. Inverse of hasFailure."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#failureBelongsTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "failure belongs to"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#first
<https://w3id.org/mqto#first> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#first> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#List> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#first> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStep> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#first> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Points to the first CountermeasureStep in a reusable ordered list. Analogous to rdf:first but defined as an explicit OWL object property with proper domain/range constraints. The list structure (rather than a direct step-to-step chain) allows the same CountermeasureStep instance to appear in multiple Countermeasure procedures without embedding order into the step itself."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#first> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "first"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#hasFailure
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasFailure> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasFailure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#IshikawaItem> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasFailure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureMode> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasFailure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Associates an IshikawaItem (Machine, Material, or Method) with a Failure Mode that can occur in that category. Establishes which failures belong to each root cause category in the fishbone diagram structure. Inverse of failureBelongsTo."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasFailure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has failure"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#hasFirstStep
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasFirstStep> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasFirstStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#hasStep> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasFirstStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureExecution> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasFirstStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStepExecution> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasFirstStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Points to the first CountermeasureStepExecution in the concrete execution chain. In the actual layer, steps are performed in a fixed linear order and are not reused, so the order is encoded directly in the chain via mqto:hasNextStep."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasFirstStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has first step"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#hasMetric
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasMetric> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasMetric> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#metricBelongsTo> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasMetric> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#IshikawaItem> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasMetric> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasMetric> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Associates an IshikawaItem (Machine, Material, or Method) with a Metric used to monitor or assess that category. Establishes which metrics are relevant for monitoring each root cause category. Inverse of metricBelongsTo."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasMetric> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has metric"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#hasNextStep
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasNextStep> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasNextStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#hasStep> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasNextStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStepExecution> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasNextStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStepExecution> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasNextStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links one CountermeasureStepExecution to the next in the concrete execution sequence. Unlike the specified layer (which uses mqto:List for reusability), the actual execution occurs once in a specific order, so step-to-step chaining is appropriate here."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasNextStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has next step"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#hasStep
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasStep> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://rds.posccaesar.org/ontology/lis14/rdl/hasActivityPart> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureExecution> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStepExecution> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a CountermeasureExecution to its constituent CountermeasureStepExecutions in the actual layer. General property for all steps; hasFirstStep identifies the starting step, and hasNextStep chains the sequence. Subproperty of lis:hasActivityPart."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#hasStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has step"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#metricBelongsTo
<https://w3id.org/mqto#metricBelongsTo> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#metricBelongsTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#metricBelongsTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#IshikawaItem> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#metricBelongsTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Associates a Metric with the IshikawaItem (Machine, Material, or Method) category it monitors or assesses. Establishes which root cause category a metric is used for. Inverse of hasMetric."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#metricBelongsTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "metric belongs to"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#metricReferredBy
<https://w3id.org/mqto#metricReferredBy> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#metricReferredBy> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#refersToMetric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#metricReferredBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#metricReferredBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureMode> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#metricReferredBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Indicates that a Metric is referred to by a Failure Mode for diagnostic purposes. Establishes which failures use which metrics for detection or characterization. Inverse of refersToMetric."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#metricReferredBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "metric referred by"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigated
<https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigated> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigated> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureExecution> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigated> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureOccurrence> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigated> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A countermeasure execution mitigated a failure occurrence. Note: this is the actual-layer forward property (past participle). The specified-layer equivalent uses mqto:mitigates (active voice). The naming difference is intentional: 'mitigated' records a completed fact at instance level, while 'mitigates' expresses a general capability at schema level."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigated> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "mitigated"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigatedBy
<https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigatedBy> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigatedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureMode> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigatedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Countermeasure> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigatedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a Failure Mode to a Countermeasure that can remediate or reduce it (specified layer). Establishes which remediation procedures are applicable for addressing specific failure types. Inverse of mitigates. The actual-layer equivalent links FailureOccurrence to CountermeasureExecution."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigatedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "mitigated by"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigates
<https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigates> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigates> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigatedBy> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigates> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Countermeasure> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigates> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureMode> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigates> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a Countermeasure to the Failure Mode(s) it can remediate or reduce (specified layer). Establishes which failure types a remediation procedure addresses. Inverse of mitigatedBy. The actual-layer equivalent links CountermeasureExecution to FailureOccurrence."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#mitigates> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "mitigates"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#providesSignal
<https://w3id.org/mqto#providesSignal> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#providesSignal> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#signalProvidedBy> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#providesSignal> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#IshikawaItem> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#providesSignal> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Signal> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#providesSignal> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates an IshikawaItem (Machine, Material, or Method) to the data channels (Signals) associated with it. A Signal may be an output channel carrying measurement data from the item (e.g. a temperature sensor reading) or an input channel carrying control data to the item (e.g. a setpoint or actuator command). The Signal is a specified channel descriptor; actual observations are made via sosa:Observation on the corresponding ActualIshikawaItem."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#providesSignal> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "provides signal"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#raised
<https://w3id.org/mqto#raised> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#raised> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#raisedBy> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#raised> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#MetricAssessment> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#raised> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureOccurrence> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#raised> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a MetricAssessment to the FailureOccurrence it detected or triggered. Establishes which failures were raised by threshold violations in metric evaluations. Inverse of raisedBy."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#raised> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "raised"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#raisedBy
<https://w3id.org/mqto#raisedBy> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#raisedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureOccurrence> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#raisedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#MetricAssessment> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#raisedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a FailureOccurrence to the MetricAssessment(s) that detected or triggered it. Establishes which metric evaluations identified the failure through threshold violations. Inverse of raised."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#raisedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "raised by"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#readBy
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readBy> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Signal> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates a Signal (data channel) to the Metric that is computed from it (specified layer). Inverse of mqto:readsFrom. For the actual-layer counterpart see mqto:evaluatedBy."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "read by"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#readsFrom
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readsFrom> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readsFrom> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#readBy> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readsFrom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readsFrom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Signal> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readsFrom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates a Metric to the Signal (data channel) it is computed from (specified layer). Inverse of mqto:readBy. For the actual-layer counterpart see mqto:evaluatesProperty."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readsFrom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "reads from"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#refersToMetric
<https://w3id.org/mqto#refersToMetric> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#refersToMetric> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureMode> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#refersToMetric> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#refersToMetric> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a Failure Mode to the Metric(s) used for its detection or characterization. Establishes which quantitative assessments are diagnostic indicators for specific failure types. Inverse of metricReferredBy."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#refersToMetric> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "refers to metric"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#rest
<https://w3id.org/mqto#rest> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#rest> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#List> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#rest> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#List> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#rest> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Points to the remainder of the ordered step list. Analogous to rdf:rest but defined as an explicit OWL object property with proper domain/range constraints for better reasoner compatibility. Together with mqto:first, this implements a reusable linked-list container so that step order is encoded in the list, not in the steps themselves. The list must terminate at mqto:nil; circular references are not permitted, though OWL cannot formally enforce acyclicity."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#rest> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "rest"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#resultProperty
<https://w3id.org/mqto#resultProperty> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#resultProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#resultProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Property> .
<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Property> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#resultProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Meta-property that specifies which data property of sosa:Result instances should be extracted and used as input for this Metric's calculation. For example, a Metric's resultProperty can point to a specific data property of the Result to extract that field from each Result instance within the specified time window. This enables multiple metrics to derive different calculations from the same observation results by selecting different result attributes. Note: This is a meta-level construct (an object property pointing to data properties), which while not ideal OWL modeling practice, provides a simple declarative mechanism for metrics to specify their input data field without requiring complex extraction rules or SPARQL property paths."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#resultProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "result property"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#signalProvidedBy
<https://w3id.org/mqto#signalProvidedBy> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#signalProvidedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Signal> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#signalProvidedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#IshikawaItem> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#signalProvidedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Associates a Signal (data channel) with the IshikawaItem (Machine, Material, or Method) that provides it. Establishes the source of measurement or control data channels. Inverse of providesSignal."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#signalProvidedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "signal provided by"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#steps
<https://w3id.org/mqto#steps> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#steps> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Countermeasure> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#steps> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#List> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#steps> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a Countermeasure to its ordered list of steps. The indirection via mqto:List enables the same CountermeasureStep to be referenced in multiple Countermeasure definitions (reuse across procedures)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#steps> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "steps"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#suggested
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggested> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggested> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#suggestedBy> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggested> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureOccurrence> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggested> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureExecution> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggested> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A failure occurrence suggested a countermeasure execution."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggested> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "suggested"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#suggestedBy
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggestedBy> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggestedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureExecution> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggestedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureOccurrence> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggestedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A countermeasure execution was suggested by a failure occurrence."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggestedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "suggested by"@en .
# 
