# #################################################################
# 
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedReason
<https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedReason> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedReason> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedReason> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Human-readable explanation of why a CountermeasureStepExecution or CountermeasureExecution was aborted before completion. Provides context for interrupted remediation procedures."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedReason> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "aborted reason"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedTime
<https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedTime> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The timestamp when a CountermeasureStepExecution or CountermeasureExecution was aborted. Records the moment the procedure was interrupted before normal completion."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "aborted time"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentValue
<https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentValue> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#MetricAssessment> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Boolean pass/fail decision resulting from comparing the calculatedValue against the Metric's threshold bounds (lowerBound/upperBound). True indicates a threshold violation (failure condition detected), false indicates normal operation within bounds."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "assessment value"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedTime
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedTime> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#MetricAssessment> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The timestamp when a MetricAssessment was computed. Marks the moment the metric calculation was performed and the threshold comparison was evaluated, which may differ from the time window of the underlying observations."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "calculated time"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedValue
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedValue> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#MetricAssessment> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The actual computed numeric value of the metric assessment. This preserves the quantitative result before threshold comparison, enabling trend analysis, statistical modeling, and root cause correlation. For example, if a temperature metric calculates 85.7°C and the upperBound is 80°C, calculatedValue is 85.7 while assessmentValue would be true (indicating a violation). The unit of measurement is inherited from the implemented Metric specification."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "calculated value"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#completionTime
<https://w3id.org/mqto#completionTime> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#completionTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStepExecution> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#completionTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#completionTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The timestamp when a CountermeasureStepExecution was successfully completed. Marks the end of a remediation step's execution. If a step is aborted, abortedTime should be used instead."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#completionTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "completion time"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#endTime
<https://w3id.org/mqto#endTime> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#endTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#endTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The timestamp when an activity or time-bound entity concluded. General-purpose temporal property applicable to various execution contexts including ProcessExecution, CountermeasureExecution, and time windows."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#endTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "end time"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#identifier
<https://w3id.org/mqto#identifier> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#identifier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#identifier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A unique identifier for an entity such as a machine serial number, material batch code, signal name, or process ID. Subproperty of dcterms:identifier. Enables correlation between ontology instances and external systems (ERP, MES, SCADA)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#identifier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "identifier"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#lowerBound
<https://w3id.org/mqto#lowerBound> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#lowerBound> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#lowerBound> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#Literal> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#lowerBound> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The minimum acceptable threshold value for a Metric. MetricAssessments compare their calculatedValue against this bound; values below the lowerBound indicate a threshold violation. Must include units compatible with the Metric's measurement context."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#lowerBound> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "lower bound"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#markdownContent
<https://w3id.org/mqto#markdownContent> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#markdownContent> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> _:genid1 .
_:genid1 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#unionOf> _:genid3 .
_:genid3 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#rest> _:genid2 .
_:genid2 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#rest> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil> .
_:genid2 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#first> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStep> .
_:genid2 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#List> .
_:genid3 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#first> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Countermeasure> .
_:genid3 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#List> .
_:genid1 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#markdownContent> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#markdownContent> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Detailed procedural instructions or documentation in Markdown format. Used for Countermeasure and CountermeasureStep to provide rich-text descriptions, images, checklists, and formatting for human-readable remediation guidance."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#markdownContent> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "markdown content"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#measValue
<https://w3id.org/mqto#measValue> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#measValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Result> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#measValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#float> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#measValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The numeric measured value contained in an Observation Result. Represents a single data point from a sensor or data source. This property can be referenced by Metric.resultProperty to extract values for metric calculations."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#measValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "measurement value"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#method
<https://w3id.org/mqto#method> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#method> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#method> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The assessment or calculation method applied by a Metric to compute its value from observations. Describes the algorithm or statistical function (e.g., 'average', 'maximum', 'standard deviation', 'trend slope') used to aggregate or analyze data within the time window."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#method> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "method"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#reasoningLine
<https://w3id.org/mqto#reasoningLine> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#reasoningLine> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureExecution> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#reasoningLine> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#reasoningLine> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Human-readable explanation of why a particular CountermeasureExecution was selected or recommended. Documents the diagnostic reasoning chain linking observed failures to the chosen remediation procedure, supporting auditability and knowledge capture."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#reasoningLine> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "reasoning line"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#role
<https://w3id.org/mqto#role> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#role> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStep> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#role> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#role> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The responsible role or job function that should perform a CountermeasureStep (e.g., 'operator', 'maintenance technician', 'quality inspector'). Enables workflow assignment and ensures appropriate expertise for remediation tasks."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#role> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "role"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#score
<https://w3id.org/mqto#score> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#score> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureExecution> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#score> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#score> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A numeric score or confidence value assigned to a CountermeasureExecution recommendation. Used by diagnostic systems to rank countermeasure suggestions based on relevance, likelihood of success, or other scoring criteria. The interpretation and scale of scores is application-specific."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#score> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "score"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#startTime
<https://w3id.org/mqto#startTime> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#startTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#startTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The timestamp when an activity or time-bound entity began. General-purpose temporal property applicable to various execution contexts including ProcessExecution, CountermeasureExecution, and time windows."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#startTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "start time"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#timeWindowSize
<https://w3id.org/mqto#timeWindowSize> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#timeWindowSize> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#timeWindowSize> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#Literal> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#timeWindowSize> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The duration of the time window over which a Metric aggregates observations for calculation. Defines how far back in time from the calculatedTime the metric should consider observation data. Typical representations include ISO 8601 durations (e.g., 'PT5M' for 5 minutes) or numeric values with implicit units."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#timeWindowSize> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "time window size"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#upperBound
<https://w3id.org/mqto#upperBound> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#upperBound> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#upperBound> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#Literal> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#upperBound> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The maximum acceptable threshold value for a Metric. MetricAssessments compare their calculatedValue against this bound; values above the upperBound indicate a threshold violation. Must include units compatible with the Metric's measurement context."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#upperBound> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "upper bound"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#viewTime
<https://w3id.org/mqto#viewTime> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#viewTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureOccurrence> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#viewTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#viewTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The timestamp when a FailureOccurrence was viewed, acknowledged, or presented to a user or system. Distinct from the actual occurrence time of the failure event itself. Used to track when failures entered human awareness or triggered system responses."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#viewTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "view time"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#weight
<https://w3id.org/mqto#weight> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#weight> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> _:genid4 .
_:genid4 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#unionOf> _:genid6 .
_:genid6 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#rest> _:genid5 .
_:genid5 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#rest> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil> .
_:genid5 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#first> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureMode> .
_:genid5 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#List> .
_:genid6 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#first> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Countermeasure> .
_:genid6 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#List> .
_:genid4 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#weight> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#int> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#weight> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A relative ranking weight assigned to a Failure Mode or Countermeasure. For Failure Modes, indicates severity or priority. For Countermeasures, indicates effectiveness or preference. Provides anchor points for external ranking logic; the ontology does not prescribe the ranking algorithm itself."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#weight> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "weight"@en .
