<https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureExecution> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The actual execution of a Countermeasure procedure, performed to mitigate one or more FailureOccurrences. Links to the Countermeasure specification via lis:implements (LIS pattern) and tracks which specific failures were addressed. As a subclass of pko:ProcedureExecution, countermeasure executions align with PKO's procedure execution model while maintaining LIS actual/specified semantics. Note: Does not directly subclass lis:Activity (which is lis:Specified), but implements Countermeasure (which is lis:Activity), maintaining the LIS distinction between specified and actual layers."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureExecution> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Countermeasure Execution"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStep
<https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStep> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.org/net/p-plan#Step> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://rds.posccaesar.org/ontology/lis14/rdl/Activity> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://rds.posccaesar.org/ontology/lis14/rdl/Specified> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A reusable specification of a single step within a Countermeasure procedure. Because the same step (e.g. 'clean the mould') may occur in multiple Countermeasures, ordering is not encoded in the step itself but in the mqto:List that references it. As a subclass of p-plan:Step, countermeasure steps align with the P-PLAN ontology for plan-based activity modeling."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Countermeasure Step"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStepExecution
<https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStepExecution> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStepExecution> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://rds.posccaesar.org/ontology/lis14/rdl/Actual> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStepExecution> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pko#StepExecution> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStepExecution> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> _:genid24 .
_:genid24 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#someValuesFrom> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStep> .
_:genid24 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty> <http://rds.posccaesar.org/ontology/lis14/rdl/implements> .
_:genid24 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStepExecution> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The actual, single execution of one CountermeasureStep. Each execution implements a specific CountermeasureStep from the specified layer via lis:implements, performed in a concrete, non-reused linear order encoded via mqto:hasFirstStep / mqto:hasNextStep, contrasting with the specified layer where mqto:List enables step reuse across procedures. As a subclass of pko:StepExecution, countermeasure step executions align with PKO's step execution model. Note: Does not directly subclass lis:Activity (which is lis:Specified), but implements CountermeasureStep (which is lis:Activity), maintaining the LIS distinction between specified and actual layers."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStepExecution> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Countermeasure Step Execution"@en .
