<https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureMode> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A manner in which a manufacturing component, system, or process could potentially fail to meet its intended function or quality requirements (specified layer). Aligns with FMEA terminology per IEC 60812:2018. Belongs to an IshikawaItem (Machine, Material, or Method category), refers to diagnostic Metrics, and can be mitigated by Countermeasures. Failure Modes can have causal relationships with other Failure Modes (causes/causedBy) to model root cause chains. The actual-layer counterpart is FailureOccurrence."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureMode> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Failure Mode"@en .
