_:genid34 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureOccurrence> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An instance-layer event representing a specific quality defect or operational problem detected during production. Implements a Failure Mode specification, appears on an ActualIshikawaItem, and is raised by one or more MetricAssessments that detected threshold violations. Can be mitigated by CountermeasureExecutions. Captures the actual occurrence with timestamps and context, as opposed to the schema-level Failure Mode definition."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureOccurrence> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Failure Occurrence"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#IshikawaItem
