_:genid66 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#Signal> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A specified data channel in the electrical-engineering sense: a named, typed signal such as a PLC variable, an analog voltage line, a fieldbus message, or a time-series data stream. A Signal may carry measurement data (sensor/output signals), control data (actuator/input signals), or both simultaneously — a setpoint, for instance, is written as a command to an actuator and can equally be read back as an observable value. It describes the metadata of the channel (identifier, unit, sampling rate, direction, etc.) rather than any particular observation or sensor device. It sits in the specified layer as the concrete data-source or data-sink binding for an abstract Metric, and is thereby distinct from sosa:ObservableProperty (which characterises an observable quality of a feature of interest in the actual layer) and from sosa:Sensor (which is the physical observing device)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#Signal> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Signal"@en .
